	<title>LIBER DECIMUS</title>
	</head>
		<div type="textpart" subtype="section">
		<head>
		<title><ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen quartum#urn:lofts:fhg.4.ctesicles.ctesiclis_fragmenta">
		CTESICLIS FRAGMENTA
		</ref></title>
		</head>
			<div type="textpart" subtype="work">
			<ab><title><ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen quartum#urn:lofts:fhg.4.ctesicles.ctesiclis_fragmenta.chronica">
			ΧΡΟΝΙΚΑ
			</ref></title></ab>
				<div type="textpart" subtype="book">
				<ab><title><ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen quartum#urn:lofts:fhg.4.ctesicles.ctesiclis_fragmenta.chronica.e_libro_tertio">
				E LIBRO TERTIO
				</ref></title></ab>
				<div type="textpart" >
				<cit n="1">
					<ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen quartum#urn:lofts:fhg.4.ctesicles.ctesiclis_fragmenta.chronica.e_libro_tertio:1">
						<bibl> Athenaeus VI, p. 272, B:</bibl>
						<quote>
						Κτησικλῆς δ ̓ ἐν τρίτῃ Χρονικῶν [τῇ πεντε]καιδεκάτῃ πρὸς ταῖς ἑκατόν φησιν Ὀλυμπιάδι Ἀθήνησιν ἐξετασμὸν γενέσθαι ὑπὸ Δημητρίου τοῦ Φαληρέως τῶν κατοικούντων τὴν Ἀττικὴν, καὶ εὑρεθῆναι Ἀθηναίους μὲν δισμυρίους πρὸς τοῖς χιλίοις, μετοίκους δὲ μυρίους, οἰκετῶν δὲ μυριάδας τεσσαράκοντα.
						</quote>
						<note type="translation"> Ctesicles tertio libro Chronicorum scribit, Olympiade [quinta] et decima cum centesima Athenis Demetrium phalereum recensum instituisse incolarum Atticae: inventosque esse civium Atheniensium millia viginti et unum, inquilinorum millia decem, servorum quadringenta millia. </note>
						<note type="commentary">[ τῇ πεντε] suppl. Schweigh., τῇ ἑκκαιδεκάτῃ volebat Casaub., τῇ ὀκτωκαιδ. Scaliger. Cf. Clinton. F. H. tom. II and Ol. 115, 4, et p. 378.</note>
					</ref>
				</cit>
				</div>
				<div type="textpart" >
				<cit n="2">
					<ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen quartum#urn:lofts:fhg.4.ctesicles.ctesiclis_fragmenta.chronica.e_libro_tertio:2">
						<bibl> Idem X, p. 445, D:</bibl>
						<quote>
						Σὺ δὲ παροινῶν καὶ μεθύων οὐδέπω κόρον ἔχεις, οὐδ ̓ ἐπὶ νοῦν λαμβάνεις, ὅτι ὑπὸ μέθης ἀπέθανεν Εὐμένης ὁ Περγαμηνὸς, ὁ Φιλεταίρου τοῦ Περγάμου βασιλεύσαντος ἀδελφιδοῦς, ὡς ἱστορεῖ Κτησικλῆς ἐν τρίτῳ Χρόνων.
						</quote>
						<note type="translation"> Te insolentiae temulentiaeque nondum satietas cepit, neque in animum tuum admittis cogitationem, ex ebrietate mortuum esse Eumenem Pergamenum, Philetaeri regis Pergameni ex fratre nepotem, ut narrat Ctesicles tertio libro Chronicorum. </note>
						<note type="commentary">Cf. Droysen. Hellenism. II, p. 368.</note>
					</ref>
				</cit>
				</div>
